---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Arizona Aikido – News and Notes">
  <section class="border-b border-slate-800 bg-slate-950/90">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-8 md:py-12">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-emerald-400">
        Dojo updates
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-50">
        News and Notes
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm md:text-base text-slate-300 max-w-2xl">
        Current announcements, seminar information, and schedule changes for Arizona Aikido.
        For weekly training times also see the Training Schedule page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-10 md:py-12 space-y-8">
    <!-- Schedule notice card -->
    <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/80 p-6 md:p-7 space-y-4">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-slate-50">
          Current class schedule in effect
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">Posted 1 December 2025</p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        The schedule below is the one in effect and replaces the schedule shown on the Training
        Schedule page. Please check here for the latest times before you come to train.
      </p>

      <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-xs md:text-sm text-slate-200">
        <li>Sunday – 10:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. – Karate</li>
        <li>Monday – 6:00 p.m. to 7:15 p.m. – Zoom class with Ikeda Sensei</li>
        <li>Tuesday – 4:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. – Aikido basics</li>
        <li>Tuesday – 5:30 p.m. to 6:30 p.m. – Aiki youth class</li>
        <li>Tuesday – 6:30 p.m. to 7:20 p.m. – Karate</li>
        <li>Wednesday – 6:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. – Weapons skills</li>
        <li>Wednesday – 7:00 p.m. to 8:00 p.m. – Low impact Aikido</li>
        <li>Thursday – 5:30 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. – Aiki youth program</li>
        <li>Thursday – 7:00 p.m. to 8:00 p.m. – Aikido open class</li>
        <li>Friday – 6:00 p.m. to 7:15 p.m. – Aikido open class</li>
        <li>Friday – 7:30 p.m. to 8:45 p.m. – Aikido</li>
        <li>Saturday – 10:45 a.m. to 11:45 a.m. – Aikido, beginner to advanced</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">
        You are welcome to wear a mask. Hand sanitizer is available and mats and surfaces are cleaned
        on a regular basis.
      </p>
    </article>

    <!-- Ikeda seminar card -->
    <article
      id="ikeda-2025"
      class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/80 p-6 md:p-7 space-y-4"
    >
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-slate-50">
          Annual Ikeda Shihan Seminar – December 12 to 14, 2025
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">Posted 13 November 2025</p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        Hiroshi Ikeda Shihan will teach a weekend seminar at Arizona Agatsu Dojo in Phoenix on
        December 12 through 14, 2025. He has supported Arizona Aikido for many years and this is a
        chance to train with him in person.
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 text-sm text-slate-200">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Location</h3>
          <p>
            Arizona Agatsu Dojo<br />
            939 W Camelback Rd<br />
            Phoenix, AZ 85013
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-400">
            Easy access from the light rail 7th Avenue station and plenty of parking on site.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Details</h3>
          <p>
            The original site provides a seminar flier and payment options, including PayPal for the
            full seminar or single sessions, and information about a Saturday night party at the
            dojo.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-400">
            When you rebuild that part, you can add buttons here for online registration and a link
            to the flier PDF.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Memorial card – Sakakibara Sensei -->
    <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/80 p-6 md:p-7 space-y-4">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-slate-50">
          Remembering Tsuneji “Tony” Sakakibara Sensei
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">Posted 22 July 2025</p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        The dojo remembers Sakakibara Sensei on the anniversary of his passing. After the death of
        Jon Takagi Sensei in 1984 he served as chief instructor, reconnected the dojo with Hombu
        Dojo in Tokyo, and helped maintain the Arizona Aikido community.
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        The original site includes photos and a note about the scholarship fund created in his name.
      </p>
    </article>

    <!-- Memorial card – O Sensei -->
    <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/80 p-6 md:p-7 space-y-4">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-slate-50">
          Remembering O Sensei
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">Posted 26 April 2025</p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        Aikido founder Morihei Ueshiba died on April 26, 1969. Arizona Aikido marks this date each
        year. The original post provides photos of his graves and links to a detailed biography and
        history of his training.
      </p>
    </article>

    <!-- You can add more older news items below in the same card style when you are ready -->
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
